 COAuthServer
 COAuthSignatureMethodA class for implementing a Signature Method See section 9 ("Signing Requests") in the spec
 COAuthSignatureMethod_HMAC_SHA1The HMAC-SHA1 signature method uses the HMAC-SHA1 signature algorithm as defined in [RFC2104] where the Signature Base String is the text and the key is the concatenated values (each first encoded per Parameter Encoding) of the Consumer Secret and Token Secret, separated by an '&' character (ASCII code 38) even if empty
 COAuthSignatureMethod_HMAC_SHA256The HMAC-SHA256 signature method uses the HMAC-SHA256 signature algorithm as defined in [RFC6234] where the Signature Base String is the text and the key is the concatenated values (each first encoded per Parameter Encoding) of the Consumer Secret and Token Secret, separated by an '&' character (ASCII code 38) even if empty
